The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Aug. 4: The rate of inflation rose to 4.67 per cent for the week ended July 22 from 4.52 per cent in the previous week, mainly due to an increase in the prices of vegetables, pulses, industrial fuel and some manufactured items. The wholesale price-based inflation stood at 4.33 per cent during the corresponding week of the previous year. The wholesale price index for all commodities was up 0.2 per cent to 204.1 points due to an increase in indices of primary articles, fuel and manufactured products. 

 New Delhi, Aug. 4: Domestic air fares will go up once again across the board from August 8, when major carriers will raise fuel surcharge on tickets to Rs 650 from Rs 500 on account of a hike in jet fuel prices.

 New Delhi, Aug. 4: Idea Cellular has received a letter of intent from the department of telecommunications (DoT) for offering services in the Mumbai metro circle.

 Mumbai, Aug. 4: Indias forex reserves increased by $675 million to $164.023 billion during the week ended July 28 against $163.348 billion in the week ended July 21.

 Jamshedpur, Aug. 4: Tata Steel has agreed to pay a 20 per cent bonus for 2005-06 to its 35,600 employees, who will be eligible to draw between Rs 8,818 and Rs 64,666 depending on their pay scale.




